public class CustomKNN
extends de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.algorithm.AbstractDistanceBasedAlgorithm<de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.data.NumberVector,de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.result.outlier.OutlierResult>
implements de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.algorithm.outlier.OutlierAlgorithm, ELKIAlgorithm<de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.data.NumberVector>
    Outlier Detection based on the distance of an object to its k nearest neighbor. This implementation differs from the original pseudocode: the k nearest neighbors do not exclude the point that is currently evaluated. I.e. for k=1 the resulting score is the distance to the 1-nearest neighbor that is not the query point and therefore should match k=2 in the exact pseudocode - a value of k=1 in the original code does not make sense, as the 1NN distance will be 0 for every point in the database. If you for any reason want to use the original algorithm, subtract 1 from the k parameter. Reference:

    S. Ramaswamy, and R. Rastogi, and K. Shim
    Efficient Algorithms for Mining Outliers from Large Data Sets.
    In: Proc. Int. Conf. on Management of Data, 2000.

    Since:
    0.3
    Author:
    Lisa Reichert
